      "settings": {
        "width": "full-width",
        "title": "",
        "text": "<h2>Green LED Lights for Command, Security & Utility Vehicles</h2><p>Green LED lights are the go-to for command vehicles, EMS supervisors, private security patrols, and utility fleets. On an active scene, a green marker signals who is in charge without extra radio traffic, and volunteer firefighters and environmental services run green wherever local code permits it. Because green separates so cleanly from primary red and blue, it stays visible in a crowded field of warning lights.</p><p>For forward warning, the<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-500-series-linear-super-led-lighthead\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Whelen Green 500 Series</span></a> and<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-700-series-super-led-lighthead\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Whelen Green 700 Series</span></a> linear lightheads throw wide-angle output from grille and surface positions, while the compact<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-micron-series-super-led-lighthead\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Green Micron Series</span></a> and<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-ion-series-super-led-universal-light\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Green ION Series</span></a> pack serious light into tight spaces. Crews that want an interior unit reach for the<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-avenger-ii-solo-single-combination-linear-tir-super-led-dash-light\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Green Avenger II SOLO dash light</span></a>, and fleets that need 360-degree coverage step up to the<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-l32-super-led-beacon\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Green L32 Super LED Beacon</span></a>. Need rear presence and traffic direction? The<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/feniex-fusion-s-200-green-lightstick\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Feniex Fusion S green lightsticks</span></a> scale from short interior runs to full-size rear sticks.</p><p>Green shows up across every duty we equip, whether you are building out<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/law-enforcement-police-lights\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">police and law enforcement lighting</span></a>, outfitting an<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/fire-ems\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">ambulance or EMS rig</span></a>, or marking a<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/public-works-construction\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">public works and construction</span></a> vehicle. Pick the color for your role, confirm your local code, and build.</p><h2>Purple LED Lights for Funeral Escort & Ceremonial Duty</h2><p>Purple LED lights own a smaller but critical niche. Across much of the country, they are tied to funeral processions, escort vehicles, and ceremonial duty, where a solemn, uncommon color tells other drivers the vehicles ahead are moving together and should not be split apart. Because purple is so rarely seen on the road, it commands attention and respect, which makes it the standard choice for both dedicated escort units and the POVs that volunteer drivers bring to the job.</p><p>Strobes N' More manufactures a dedicated purple line for exactly this work. The<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/strobes-n-more-purple-e-series-led\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Purple E Series grille LED</span></a> and its<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/strobes-n-more-dual-purple-e-series-led\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">dual-head version</span></a> mount behind the grille for a clean look with strong forward output, and for the windshield the<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/strobes-n-more-purple-dash-led\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Purple Dash LED</span></a>,<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/strobes-n-more-purple-dual-dash-led\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Purple Dual Dash LED</span></a>, and<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/products/strobes-n-more-purple-dual-linear-dash-led\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Purple Dual Linear Dash LED</span></a> give escort drivers warning-grade brightness that transfers between vehicles in minutes. That is the reason these dash units are a favorite on POVs run by off-duty personnel and volunteer escort drivers who need purple without a permanent install.</p><h2>Match the Light to Your Mount</h2><p>Color gets you noticed, but the mount decides how the light fits your vehicle, so it pays to choose the form factor first. Front-facing<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/surface-mount-and-grille-led-lights\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">grille and surface mounts</span></a> install on the front of the vehicle for direct forward warning, while<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/dash-window-mount\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">dash and window lights</span></a> sit inside the cab and swap between vehicles in seconds, which is why they dominate POV setups. For a stealth build,<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/hide-away-leds\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">hideaway strobes</span></a> tuck into existing housings and disappear until they flash. Add length and pattern control at the rear with<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/led-stick-lights\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">LED stick lights</span></a> or a<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/mini-lightbars\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">mini lightbar</span></a>, or get full roof coverage from a<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/360-beacons\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">360-degree beacon</span></a> for slow-moving and stationary work.</p><p>Running a dual-purpose vehicle? Pair your green or purple lightheads with<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/amber-lights\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">amber warning lights</span></a> to cover construction and utility duty in the same build, wherever your code allows the combination.</p><h2>Know the Rules Before You Install</h2><p>Color laws vary widely by state and by vehicle type, and what an EV can run is often different from what a POV can run. Some states restrict green or purple to specific vehicle classes, permit them only for certain duties, or require a permit, while others allow color combinations for command and specialty vehicles. Always confirm your state and local regulations before you install and operate purple or green warning lights, and check each product listing for SAE and NFPA certifications when compliance is on the line.</p><p>Not sure how to wire or position a light? Our<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/pages/install-guides\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">install guides</span></a> and<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/blogs/instructional-videos\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">instructional videos</span></a> walk through the common setups; our<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/pages/installation-service\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">installation team</span></a> can handle the full build for you, and the<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/blogs/informative\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">informative blog</span></a> digs deeper into vehicle lighting and color use. Buying for a fleet? The<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/pages/dealers\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">dealer program</span></a> covers volume pricing, or you can<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/pages/contact\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">reach out with a specific vehicle question</span></a> any time.</p><h2>Built With Trusted Warning-Light Brands</h2><p>This collection pulls from the brands responders trust, including<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/whelen-products\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Whelen</span></a> for premium linear and beacon output,<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/feniex\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Feniex</span></a> for versatile lightsticks,<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/federal-signal\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Federal Signal</span></a> for interior dash lighting,<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/soundoff-signal\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">SoundOff Signal</span></a> for hideaway systems, and<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/ecco\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">ECCO</span></a> for jobsite-focused warning lights. The purple grille and dash options here come straight from the<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/strobes-n-more\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Strobes N' More E Series</span></a>, which we design and build in-house.</p>",
        "heading_size": "medium",
        "text_alignment": "left"
      }
    },
